 Wait Beats: 12
 Can Learn: FALSE
Noun Damage: root touch
   Wear-Off: !Root Touch!
Acquisition:
   - Druid: level 1
Description:
   Root Touch is the most basic expression of the Overgrowth Doctrine: the
   Druid channels living-world vitality through their own body into a contact
   strike. The life force of the living world briefly extends through the
   practitioner's hands. At level 1 this is undirected and inefficient — the
   technique costs more than the result justifies, which the tradition accepts
   as a consequence of incomplete covenant.

   Like all Druid spells, Root Touch costs hit points rather than mana
   (Overgrowth mechanic, growth = 3 HP per cast). Damage: 2d4, earth
   elemental. Does not scale with level — the Druid's control over this
   technique is limited at early levels. A successful save halves damage.

   Druids with higher constitution sustain this at lower relative cost.
   Root Touch is superseded by Thornlash (level 3) for sustained offense.
